correctness.rationale: Major factual and schema issues. Key problems: (1) Missing processes: the article reports three ALD temperatures (130, 150, 170 °C) with distinct properties; only one process (150 °C) is extracted. (2) Schema violations: 'plasmaPower' is set to null but must be an object or omitted; filmDensity uses unit GM-PER-DeciM3 (g/dm³) with value 5.9, which corresponds to 5.9 g/dm³ instead of the reported 5.9 g/cm³ (should be 5900 g/dm³ if that unit is used). (3) Incorrect or misinterpreted values: 'thresholdVoltage' = 0.6 V is actually the PBS ΔVth shift, not Vth; 'electricalProperties.mobility' is listed as 10.4 cm²/V·s with four‑point probe as the method—mobility was extracted from TFT transfer characteristics, while four‑point probe measured conductivity; 'deviceStructure' should be 'top-gate bottom-contact'. (4) Non-traceable/guessed parameters: reactor pressure (1 mTorr), growth-per-cycle (0.18 Å), dosing/purge times, flow rates, 'saturation', 'nucleationPeriod', refractive index, absorption coefficient, resistivity, carrier density, uniformity (5%), conformality (aspect ratio 10), safety/reproducibility booleans—none are reported in the article. (5) Supercycle design/specification: 'numberofSubcycles' = 1 for InGaOx and ZnO and 'subcycleSequence' are not given in the article; 'numberofCycles' = 120 refers to supercycles in the text, not total ALD cycles as used here. (6) Composition reporting: 'elementalConcentration' 33.3% is incorrect for the stated 1:1:3 ratio (would be ~20%, 20%, 60% if converted); 'crystallinity' method is set to XRD, but the article does not report XRD. (7) Carrier/purging gas: nitrogen is only stated as purge gas; listing it also as carrier gas is not supported by the text. Corrections needed: add separate processes for 130, 150, and 170 °C with traceable values (film thickness, band gap, roughness, mobility, on/off ratio); remove or leave unspecified any parameters not reported; omit 'plasmaPower' instead of null; fix filmDensity unit/value; remove misassigned 'thresholdVoltage' or replace with actual Vth if reported; align mobility and its method under deviceProperties; correct deviceStructure; omit speculative supercycle counts; revise composition reporting to match the 1:1:3 ratio and omit unsupported elemental %s.

completeness.rationale: Major incompleteness and schema issues. (1) Multiple processes missing: the article reports IGZO ALD at 130, 150, and 170 °C with distinct film thicknesses (21.4, 24.3, 27.4 nm), band gaps (3.81, 3.26, 3.21 eV), roughness (0.30, 0.34, 0.46 nm) and device mobilities (6.1, 10.4, 14.8 cm2/V·s). Only a single process (150 °C) is extracted, violating the requirement to represent each experiment. (2) Numerous values are ungrounded or incorrect: reactor pressure (1 mTorr), dosing/purge times, flow rates, growth-per-cycle, nucleation period, saturation, uniformity variation, conformality aspect ratio, refractive index, absorption coefficient, film resistivity and carrier density are not reported in the article; thresholdVoltage = 0.6 V misuses the PBS shift (ΔVth = +0.6 V) as the absolute VTH; film mobility under materialProperties is not reported (device μ is reported instead); crystallinity method “XRD” is not mentioned. (3) Schema violation: plasmaPower is set to null, but the schema expects an object if present. (4) Supercycle design specifics (number of subcycles and sequence) are not provided in the article; assigning counts and sequence is ungrounded, and the article’s “120 supercycles” is conflated with total ALD cycles. To improve completeness, add three separate process entries (130/150/170 °C) with traceable values for film thickness, band gap, roughness, density, and device metrics; remove or mark as not reported any parameters not provided (pressure, dosing/purge/flows, GPC, nucleation, uniformity, conformality, resistivity, carrier density, refractive index, absorption); correct thresholdVoltage to omit or provide the actual value if reported; remove plasmaPower or provide a valid object only if PEALD is used; keep supercycle count and description only as supported by the text (‘120 supercycles; supercycle composed of In–Ga–O and Zn–O’).
